  "text": "All log compaction implementation files reside under storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/. The architecture breaks down as follows:\n\n1. **Cleaner thread**: `LogCleaner.java` is the top-level orchestrator (implements BrokerReconfigurable) and contains an inner class `CleanerThread` (extends ShutdownableThread) that runs the background cleaner threads.\n\n2. **Segment selection policy**: `LogCleanerManager.java` manages which log partitions are eligible for cleaning and tracks their cleaning state. `LogToClean.java` is a helper that represents a cleanable log with its dirty ratio, used for prioritizing which partitions to clean. `LogCleaningState.java` is a sealed interface defining the possible states (in-progress, aborted, paused).\n\n3. **Key-based deduplication logic**: `Cleaner.java` holds the actual cleaning/deduplication logic \u2014 it iterates over log segments, builds an offset map of keys, and writes deduplicated output. `OffsetMap.java` is the interface for the key\u2192offset hash map, and `SkimpyOffsetMap.java` is the production implementation using cryptographic hashing (MD5) for space-efficient key deduplication.\n\n4. **Supporting files**: `CleanerConfig.java` (configuration), `CleanerStats.java` / `PreCleanStats.java` (metrics), `CleanedTransactionMetadata.java` (transaction handling during compaction), and `LogCleaningAbortedException.java` / `LogCleaningException.java` (exceptions).",
